"tree": "Katy Apple Tree",
 "DESCRIPTION": "Apple Katy is a Swedish variety from 1947, also known as Apple Katja and produces heavy crops of bright red fruit. The flavour is sweet and sometimes strawberry-like. When picked straight from the tree Apple Katy has an incredibly juicy refreshing taste. Apple Katy is often used for juicing, with the juice being slightly dry and very refreshing.

Crops of bright red apples are produced in early September. A pollinator is required in group A, B or C within a half mile radius. Apple Katy will suit less than perfect and/or Northern positions. Katy is a popular variety so we offer it in M27 rootstocks (very dwarf - ideal for growing in pots and tiny gardens) as well as our usual M26 (semi dwarf) and MM106 (semi vigorous)."
